# Nova Motion — Cursor Instructions
# Drop this file as `.cursorrules` in the project root.
# Cursor reads it automatically on every prompt.

## Project Overview
Nova Motion is a boutique Pilates studio website.
Stack: React 18, Vite, React Router v6, plain CSS (no Tailwind, no UI library).
All styles come from `src/styles/globals.css` via CSS custom properties.

---

## Architecture Rules

### Routing
- All routes are defined in `src/App.jsx` using BrowserRouter + Routes.
- Each route maps to one file in `src/pages/`.
- Never add `<Link>` or `useNavigate` logic inside `src/sections/` — pass callbacks from pages instead.
- Scroll-to-top on route change is handled by `<ScrollToTop />` in App.jsx — do not duplicate it.

### State
- Cart state lives in `src/hooks/useCart.js` — do not duplicate cart logic anywhere else.
- All modal open/close state and booking state lives in `App.jsx` (`Shell` component) and is passed down as props.
- Never use localStorage, sessionStorage, or any browser storage APIs — keep all state in React memory.

### Data
- All site content (classes, schedule, products, membership, team) lives in `src/data/`.
- To add or edit content, modify only the data files — never hard-code content in components.
- Image paths are set as an `image` field in the data files (e.g. `src/data/classes.js`). When `image` is null, the `<ImagePlaceholder>` component renders automatically.

---

## Styling Rules

### Always use CSS variables — never raw hex or pixel values inline
```jsx
// CORRECT
color: "var(--color-gold)"
background: "var(--color-bg-dark)"
border: "1px solid var(--color-border)"

// WRONG
color: "#b8975a"
background: "#1c1c1c"
```

### Full list of CSS variables (defined in src/styles/globals.css)
```
Fonts:
  --font-display   Cormorant Garamond (serif headings)
  --font-body      DM Sans (all body text, labels, buttons)

Backgrounds:
  --color-bg         #f7f4ef  (page default, warm off-white)
  --color-bg-warm    #f0ebe2  (section tint, slightly darker)
  --color-bg-card    #fffcf8  (card surfaces)
  --color-bg-dark    #1c1c1c  (dark sections: schedule, footer, testimonials)
  --color-bg-dark-2  #242424  (nested dark surfaces)

Text:
  --color-text       #1c1c1c  (headings, primary)
  --color-text-mid   #4a4542
  --color-text-muted #6e6560  (body copy)
  --color-text-faint #8c857e  (labels, metadata)
  --color-text-inv   #f7f4ef  (text on dark backgrounds)

Accent:
  --color-gold       #b8975a  (primary brand accent)
  --color-gold-dark  #9e7e46  (hover state for gold)

Borders:
  --color-border      #e8e2d8
  --color-border-dark #2a2a2a

Shadows:
  --shadow-card  0 12px 32px rgba(28,28,28,0.08)
  --shadow-lift  0 20px 50px rgba(28,28,28,0.12)

Motion:
  --transition      0.25s ease
  --transition-slow 0.4s ease
```

### Button classes (use these — do not create new button styles)
```
.btn-primary   dark fill, gold on hover
.btn-outline   transparent with dark border, fills on hover
.btn-gold      gold fill, darker on hover
.btn-ghost     no border/background, for icon buttons
```

### Typography classes
```
.section-label    small gold uppercase eyebrow text
.display-heading  Cormorant Garamond serif heading
.body-text        DM Sans 15px/300 weight body copy
```

### Animation utility classes
```
.fade-up   fadeUp 0.7s  (elements entering from below)
.fade-in   fadeIn 0.6s
.slide-dn  slideDown 0.3s (dropdowns, expanded content)
```

### Card / interactive element classes
```
.class-card       class grid card with left accent bar on hover
.product-card     shop product card
.membership-card  pricing card (add .featured for dark variant)
.schedule-slot    timetable row (add .booked for confirmed state)
.filter-chip      pill-style filter button
.day-btn          schedule day tab button
```

### Form inputs
```
<input  className="form-input" />
<textarea className="form-input" />
```

### Modals
```
.overlay    full-screen dark backdrop
.modal      centred modal card
.modal-close   close button (✕)
.cart-panel    slide-in right drawer
.toast         bottom-centre notification
```

---

## Component Guidelines

### ImagePlaceholder
Use `<ImagePlaceholder>` whenever rendering an image that might not exist yet.
```jsx
import ImagePlaceholder from "@/components/ImagePlaceholder";

{item.image
  ? <img src={item.image} alt={item.name} style={{ width:"100%", height:200, objectFit:"cover" }} />
  : <ImagePlaceholder label="product-name.jpg" height="200px" accent={item.accent} />
}
```
Props: `label` (string), `height` (css string), `width` (css string), `accent` (hex), `round` (boolean for circle crop).

### PageHero
All inner pages start with PageHero:
```jsx
import PageHero from "@/components/PageHero";
<PageHero label="Section" title="Page Title" subtitle="Optional subtitle." />
```
Optional `bgImage` prop for a full-bleed photo background.

### Toast notifications
Call `showToast(message)` — it lives in `App.jsx` Shell and is passed down as `onToastShow`.
Never create a second toast system.

### Modals
Open a modal by setting state in App.jsx (e.g. `setClassModal(cls)`).
All modal components are in `src/components/` and receive props from App.jsx.

---

## File Naming Conventions
```
src/pages/         PascalCase + "Page" suffix   e.g. AboutPage.jsx
src/sections/      PascalCase noun              e.g. Testimonials.jsx
src/components/    PascalCase noun              e.g. CartPanel.jsx
src/data/          camelCase noun               e.g. classes.js
src/hooks/         camelCase "use" prefix       e.g. useCart.js
src/styles/        kebab-case                   e.g. globals.css
```

---

## Path Aliases
`@` maps to `src/`. Always use it for imports:
```js
// CORRECT
import { CLASSES } from "@/data/classes";
import PageHero from "@/components/PageHero";

// WRONG
import { CLASSES } from "../../data/classes";
```

---

## Do Not
- Do not install UI libraries (no shadcn, no MUI, no Chakra, no Radix).
- Do not add Tailwind — styling is done with inline styles + globals.css classes only.
- Do not use localStorage or sessionStorage.
- Do not add global state management (no Redux, no Zustand) — React state + props is enough.
- Do not create new CSS files — add to globals.css or use inline styles.
- Do not hard-code content strings in JSX — put them in src/data/ files.
- Do not add routing logic inside sections/ files.
- Do not duplicate cart, toast, or modal logic — they're centralised in App.jsx.

---

## Adding a New Page
1. Create `src/pages/NewPage.jsx`
2. Add the route in `src/App.jsx` inside `<Routes>`:
   ```jsx
   <Route path="/new-page" element={<NewPage />} />
   ```
3. Add the nav link in `src/components/Navbar.jsx` NAV_LINKS array.
4. Add the footer link in `src/components/Footer.jsx` COLS array.
5. Start the page with `<PageHero label="..." title="..." subtitle="..." />`.

---

## Adding a New Section
1. Create `src/sections/NewSection.jsx`.
2. Import data from `src/data/` — do not hard-code content.
3. Use CSS variables for all colours and spacing tokens.
4. Export a single default function component.
5. Import and use it in the relevant page file.

---

## Common Patterns

### Filterable grid
```jsx
const [filter, setFilter] = useState("All");
const visible = filter === "All" ? items : items.filter(i => i.category === filter);
```

### Expandable card (click to reveal bio/detail)
```jsx
const [activeId, setActiveId] = useState(null);
onClick={() => setActiveId(activeId === item.id ? null : item.id)}
{activeId === item.id && <div className="slide-dn">...</div>}
```

### Booking a schedule slot
```jsx
// In App.jsx Shell:
const handleBook = (slot, day) => setBookingSlot({ slot, day });
// Pass onBook={handleBook} to Schedule/SchedulePage
```

---

## Image Slots Quick Reference
Search for `📸` in any file to find every image placeholder.

| Data file              | Field to add    | Folder                              |
|------------------------|-----------------|-------------------------------------|
| src/data/classes.js    | image           | src/assets/images/classes/          |
| src/data/products.js   | image           | src/assets/images/products/         |
| src/data/team.js       | image           | src/assets/images/instructors/      |
| src/sections/Hero.jsx  | backgroundImage | src/assets/images/hero/             |
| src/sections/About.jsx | studioImg       | src/assets/images/about/            |
| src/sections/Testimonials.jsx | avatar | src/assets/images/testimonials/     |
